theorem open_closure_interior_implies_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hOpen : IsOpen (closure (interior (A : Set X)))) :
    Topology.P3 (A : Set X) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- `x` lies in `closure (interior A)` by density of the closure.
  have hx_cl : x ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := subset_closure hxA
  -- Since this closure is open, its interior equals itself.
  have hIntEq :
      interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))) =
        closure (interior (A : Set X)) := hOpen.interior_eq
  -- Reinterpret the membership using the equality.
  have hx_int :
      x ∈ interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))) := by
    simpa [hIntEq] using hx_cl
  -- Monotonicity of `interior` and `closure` yields the desired inclusion.
  have hIncl :
      interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))) ⊆
        interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
    interior_closure_interior_subset_closure (A := A)
  exact hIncl hx_int

theorem closure_interior_univ_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    closure (interior (Set.univ : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  simpa [interior_univ, closure_univ]
